{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, one can extend this analysis to intuitionistic and classical modal logic based on Beth-style semantics.There is a deeper perspective on this connection between Beth semantics and possibility semantics, explored in Bezhanishvili andHolliday 2016, 2019.",
    "Given a frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, P, Q⟩ as above, consider the Heyting algebra H(S, ⊑) of all downsets in ⟨S, ⊑⟩.",
    "Then consider the function j on H(S, ⊑) such that for any downset O, j(O) = {x ∈ S | ∀Z ∈ Q(x) ∃z ∈ Z: z ∈ O}.",
    "Dragalin shows (pp.",
    "72-3, using 'D' instead of 'j') that this j is a closure operator on H(S, ⊑) in the sense of lattice theory [Davey and Priestley, 2002, § 7.1], i.e., where ≤ is the natural order on the algebra, we have that for all elements a and b of the algebra: a ≤ b implies j(a) ≤ j(b); a ≤ j(a); and j(j(a)) = j(a)."
  ]
}